1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,145
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:11,929
First, you do a warm-up: You open Word, clicks the page, and watches for the flashing cursor.

3
00:00:11,929 --> 00:00:16,508
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

4
00:00:16,508 --> 00:00:25,720
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Build one sentence together: capital letter, words, spaces and full stop.

5
00:00:25,720 --> 00:00:31,046
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type a full sentence.

6
00:00:31,046 --> 00:00:37,173
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Press Enter and add another sentence.

7
00:00:37,173 --> 00:00:41,548
Staff supports punctuation only after the idea is typed.

8
00:00:41,548 --> 00:00:44,099
Take one activity at a time.

9
00:00:44,099 --> 00:00:48,641
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

